PrecisSetting apart for the use and benefit of the KAPAWE'NO FIRST NATION BAND, as Grouard Indian Reserves No. 229, 230 and 231, of some 1,097 hectares of land situated on and near LESSER SLAVE LAKE in Alberta, together with all the mines and minerals which may be found to exist within, upon or under those lands.
